INTRODUCTION Stereotypes and miscommunication have led to many misunderstandings between people of different cultures. As the world beeomes increasingly multicultural, new tools are needed to educate populations about each other. The multimedia, interactive computer environment could be one such tool as it transforms the computer from a technical medium to a communications medium. However, the role of interface design in these environments needs to expand from the traditional role of facilitating ease of computer use to a role that incorporates the communicative power of new technological resources. In this new role, interface design can not only educate users how to use multimedia systems but also has the potential to educate people about each other.